                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1103">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/9808.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador to Spain</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-11-18T14:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 18, 1913—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s November 10, 2 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d1103fn1">See footnote to the
                        telegram of November 7, 10 p.m.</note> The Spanish Cabinet is still
                    considering the subject thereof and may continue indefinitely. The German
                    Ambassador and the French Chargé d’Affaires here tell me that their respective
                    Governments will take no independent action and each is in accord with our
                    Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Willard</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
